                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fæzzæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzæg</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>осень</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>autumn</q></tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzygon</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>autumn (adj.)</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>in autumn</q></tr></sense></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzygænd</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>озимь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>winter crop</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>озимая вспашка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>immature cones</q></tr></sense></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ærægvæzzæg</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>поздняя осень</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>late autumn</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>næ fæzzæg k˳ystæn ū</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наша осень — (пора) работы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>out autumn is working time</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fæzzæg ærcydīs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наступила осень</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>autumn came</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>kud ǧæzdug æj næ fæzzæg!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как обильна наша осень!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>how abundant our autumn is!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III 5</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>næ fæzzæg k˳ystæn ū</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наша осень — (пора) работы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>out autumn is working time</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fæzzæg ærcydīs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наступила осень</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>autumn came</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>kud ǧæzdug æj næ fæzzæg!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как обильна наша осень!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>how abundant our autumn is!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III 5</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Как и названия других времен года, — иранское слово (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_walʒæg"/> ‘весна’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_særd"/> ‘лето’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zymæg"/> ‘зима’). Возводится к %i*pati-zyaka-%i, где %ipati%i — предлог со значением ‘к’, а %izyaka%i — от %izyam%i ‘зима’: осень определяется как время года, когда дело идет „к зиме“. Развитие формы: %i*pati-zyaka-%i → %i*fajzyak%i → %ifæzzæg%i (%ipati%i → %ifaj%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fajnūst"/>; %ijz%i → %izz%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> из %ibajzajyn%i и др.). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>paīz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>pātez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-pazend"><lang/> <w>pādez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/> <w>pij</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*patīz- (ptyz)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>paša</w> <gloss><q>осень</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XII 329 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XII 329 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Iranian word, like the names of other seasons (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_walʒæg"/> ‘spring’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_særd"/> ‘summer’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zymæg"/> ‘winter’). It traces back to %i*pati-zyaka-%i, where %ipati%i is a preposition with the meaning ‘to’, and %izyaka%i is from %izyam%i ‘winter’: autumn is defined as the time of year when it is going on for winter. The form development: %i*pati-zyaka-%i → %i*fajzyak%i → %ifæzzæg%i (%ipati%i → %ifaj%i, as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fajnūst"/>; %ijz%i → %izz%i, as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> from %ibajzajyn%i etc.). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>paīz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>pātez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-pazend"><lang/> <w>pādez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/> <w>pij</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*patīz- (ptyz)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>paša</w> <gloss><q>autumn</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XII 329 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XII 329 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>